content.description: Sit start the same for power struggle but keep going left to a big jug and dons big move to a good hold and traverse back right to the mantle of power struggle
content.location: Same boulder as Power Struggle

content.description: Cool slab with a funky top out pretty straight forward just go up the middle
content.protection: Pads, don’t really wanna fall off this one up high since you’ll roll down a hill if you’re not careful.
content.location: at the top of the hill behind the casting couch

content.description: Left of pumped up blocks, start up the rightward sloping crack
content.location: Left of pumped up blocks

content.description: Start low with a left hand sloper and right crimp on the underside, climb up through crimps and slap the edge, heel up and bump to the pinch. Crux is going from that to the hold near the top. One of the best here so far
content.location: Behind chromatic abberation wall up the hill a bit, it’s a huge house sized boulder.

content.description: Start on the flat saucer at the bottom and move your way up and left some hard moves to a jug hueco. Finish here or clip in and climb the head wall which adds a tough headwall. This has to be one of the coolest boulders in central AZ let alone the state.
content.location: A hundredish feet to the right of power struggle. Best to start from there and go around the that  boulder and scramble/head to the right until you come up to the cave

content.description: Start in the crack and do a bud dead point or dyno into the higher crack and finish straight up.
content.location: Left of jailhouse rock, other end of the same boulder as black line

content.description: Start is the crux with a left foot and stand up to get your right foot on then use a right hand high casting to reach straight up and mantle
content.location: Being ethical chipping right to the left of the little slab to get up to power struggle

content.description: Start right hand on the left leaning sloper (this is the left hand start for Dimple Dance), and left on a sharp crimp. Move up past and undercling and top out.
content.location: In the center on the hatching boulder

content.description: Layback about 8 feet of hand crack in a shallow left facing dihedral to the top of the right block. From here climb the finger crack over the lip. A high left foot got me over the lip.
content.location: From the parking near the jailhouse boulder, walk to the southern wash. The route is fairly obvious from the bottom of the wash.

content.description: cool little boulder. climb the left side.
content.location: go up and behind the area with the sport climbs and keep heading right. you will not miss the large hollow rock that looks like a spartan helmet.

content.description: Climb just right of the USC&GS SURVEY '33 inscription on the jailhouse boulder.
content.location: Right of Jailhouse Rock

content.description: Start on the left end of a flake, go up a seam through a little chute. Avoid chimneying at the top
content.location: Left of danger mantle, under the featureless slab roof on the boulder that houses the 'black streak'

content.description: Same start as me let but move left to the end and up
content.location: Small boulder in front of power struggle

content.description: on the far right end of the jailhouse boulder, enter the cave and look above your head for a big block jug, start here. Invert and foot jam the crack, moving left onto the crystal face of the jailhouse boulder, and up.
content.location: On the big boulder with the jail cell under it, right of the jail cell

content.description: The crux is getting over the bulge. Start in the cramp rail and bump your right hand to a sloper then do another big bump around the corner to a jug. Bring left hand up and get a high left foot (heel or toe) them stand up and top out.
content.location: Boulder to the right of rage quit.

content.description: Start matched in the hueco and do a big move out to the rail and mantle up from there, area classic!
content.location: Behind the main big boulder with the cave, boulder is the one with the huge hueco hole in the middle

content.description: Start on the blank looking wall under the small roof and follow the bolts up
content.location: From the parking boulder look left, it's on the big brown ridge. It is about a 10 minute walk watch out for cactus! Follow the ridge until there is a flat rocky spot at the base.

content.description: On the main boulder when you arrive you can walk along the other boulders to the top to set up a top rope of 2 bolts. Start to the right of the cave and stay left of the bulge, the line doesn't use the bulge and is only the slab itself
content.protection: 2 longer draws for a toprope, or a few boulder pads.

content.description: Start left and traverse into the crack because of the obvious pricked bush underneath the crack
content.location: From jail house rock there’s a boulder pile across the wash and some bushes. you need to hike through the wash to get to it.

content.description: Start on the lowest part of the rail same as for zig zag and follow the rail to 2 small crimps and throw big, then go straight up and mantle and climb the slab to the top. Grading this one is really hard because it’s very subjective to size and strength. Great boulder regardless.
content.protection: Pad and spotter. Don’t fall on The slab
content.location: From the main boulder by the parking area take the trail down to the left, take that until it branches right. The trail ends and becomes a scramble. Once at the top turn left and you should be at a flat spot with sand

content.description: Start same as rage quit, move left to arête and climb up!
content.location: Same boulder as rage quit

content.description: Start on right crack same as true grit but just go straight up and top out to the right.
content.location: On the north face of a Big boulder down to the left of the parking area just left of rage quit.

content.description: start on the arete and reach up to a razor crimp out right you can use to slap up the arete and do some big moves to get to the top. sit start bumps it up a v point.
content.location: Left side overhanging arete on jailhouse rock boulder

content.description: Jump start to a flat jug over the death pit underneath, climb a few moves to a pretty good sidepull then launch up 7 feet (dont know how to grade dyno's, its really hard) to the next jug and top out with a v4 boulder problem straight up.
content.protection: Top rope anchors and a directional since a fall on lead would cause you to deck on the boulders behind you. Do this as a boulder/solo you'll be cooler than Honnold.
content.location: You can see it up and to the left of the jail house rock boulder right when you get to the climbing area. Scramble some rocks until you get to it.

content.description: Sit start on the crack to the right and do the Cool traverse to the end of the crack to a slightly tricky top out.
content.location: From casting couch take the wash to the left around the hill directly behind it and it will be on the back side of said hill.

content.description: Start on the jug and go to a right Gaston and a left hand side pull to the top
content.location: On the backside of the small boulder right in front of power struggle

content.description: Climb the Left most arete to the top
content.location: left of main jailhouse rock boulder same boulder as black line, true grit, Nederlander.

content.description: Start with your feet on the triangle platform thing and move up and left to some good crimps and then continue up crimps to the top
content.location: In a little alcove up and back a bit from mirrors edge

content.description: Just found it on an exploratory trip and thought I’d add it here so I don’t forget about it when this place cools down, but it starts off a jug undercling with bad feet, go up to a bad left Gaston and get a foot up, then go to a right hand razor crimp and shoot to the lip. Really short and powerful. Placeholder grade until I try it
content.location: Behind the main jail house rock boulder when you first get there in the amphitheater looking area

content.description: Left side of the power struggle boulder, climb up the jugs, be cautious of loose/crumbly rock
content.location: Power struggle boulder

content.description: Start on the sloper and move out left get a high foot and make a big move to a jug, from there you catch a crimp rail in move up onto a ledge, after that you have some crimpy climbing, stay left of the flakes (I climbed this before I really knew what climbing was and completely defiled this with yellow paint like I was marking holds in the gym. Nothing else here has ever gotten that treatment and I've grown a lot and am working on un-messing up this thing)
content.location: To the right of the jail house rock boulder, you will see a pathway under a few boulder. Make your way under them to a shade area with a flat boulder in the middle. The route goes just up to the huge ledge.

content.description: On the big rock with the small cave,Start to the right of the cave on the small ledge. Climb left using the bulge.
content.protection: There are 2 old bolts on the top that are safe although they look sketchy, most can boulder the climb but if you prefer rope you can scramble up the rocks to the right to get on top, it is a good set up to learn how to setup a top rope or repel
content.location: Right in front of the circular parking area

content.description: Some really fun moves, The start is down on the ground but the belayer stays above you. You don't have to start at the bottom but it is more fun. the start is really easy slab climbing to a small roof with the first crux getting up to a small arete. after the arete and a great rest the next crux is right after with a large move to a jug then get a realy high foot and reach the crack. after that it leads to easier terrain and a top out.
content.protection: a few bolts, anchors and chains at the top.
content.location: by desert dime.

content.description: SDS low on the crimp rail and move right to the jug. Reach up to the lip and once standing on the lower jug, toss your left foot on the the rail and mantle up.
content.location: To the right of danger mantle

content.description: Start at the obvious circle and bring a left hand up to a micro rail, hand foot match the circle and crank hard to a slopey crimp and bump up to the pretty good slopey jug. Match and do a hard crossover undercling thing and top out. (Tried in the heat and could barely do any moves yet, so cooler temps and being strong will help see if it’s possible, grade just an estimate at the time)
content.protection: There’s a bolt to try the moves since you don’t really wanna fall unless you got a bunch of pads and a spotter due to the rock ledge thing.
content.location: Around the backside of the hill from underbelly you’ll see it to your right. Casting couch will be a few hundred feet forward if you keep going straight.

content.description: Start with a left hand sidepull and right hand undercling, bump that left up to another sidepull pinch thing and dons big move to a good hold with your right and top it
content.location: on the back of the closest rock pile to the trail leading up to the wall with chromatic aberration.

content.description: Left hand sloper right hand good block crimp, follow the orange streak all the way up. Bring your arm span for this one. (placeholder grade for now but can’t see it getting easier than that, especially for shorter people)
content.location: To the left of the jail house boulder 30 or so feet, can’t miss it.

content.description: Crimp rail up to a sloping sidepull, then good holds up top
content.protection: It's a short boulder but it’s on a ledge, you can go to the top and set up top rope anchor around a boulder up top to work the moves.
content.location: From the parking area by the jail house boulder continue on the trail until you see it up on your right.

content.description: Cool little slab traverse from left or right. You get to use a few drilled pockets that were out there long ago by whoever was doing the quarrying out here.
content.location: Past cheese grater on the way to power struggle

content.description: Start low in the two obvious hand sized dishes and go up to the ledgeContinuing up to the top from the ledge looks fun, but more of a solo
content.location: right of jazz in the alcove, look for the geocache

content.description: Subtle voorwerk is the name of the game. Start with hands on two left leaning slopers, and find your feet. The start is the hardest.
content.location: On the right side of the hatching boulder

content.description: Start in the torso sized dish on the far left, hands matched on the rail above. move right onto the face and up along the left edge.
content.location: When passing through the tunnel to access the alcove, the hatching boulder is on your right

content.description: Start off the baby crimp left and jug ledge right And go up!
content.location: To the right of desert dime, walk under the leaning boulder and its on the other side

content.description: Start of the slopey jugs and work your way up!
content.location: Instead of turning off left to get to jail house keep forward until you reach a big rock pile on your left, walk up to it and find the bolts, same formation as chromatic abberation (update Nov20 old bolts removed will rebolt with new hardware soon. Top Rope is still good.)

content.description: Start on the crack Rail and follow right to the end and go straight up from there to a cool mantle
content.location: Directly behind rage quit up some rocks a bit and you’ll see it

content.description: Start on the arete right of checkpoint and follow it up. (Other variants can link into another route and head right to the face or vice versa)
content.location: The farm boulder. See route “checkpoint” for location.

content.description: Start either on the ground or on the flat boulder that nearly touches the slab. Climb up the left side of the face using the holds around the left lip. Easy, but a fall could crunch you between the slab and the flat rock at the base
content.location: Boulder behind the hatching boulder, on the north side

content.description: Start and follow the left crack just right of the arete
content.location: Left of parking area north facing side of the big boulder directly left of rage quit

content.description: SDS in the hole with the hand crack above you. top out straight up.
content.location: In the alcove, when facing Jazz and Ensemble, look to the left and behind you

content.description: Start with the jug undercling and move up the almost blank black streak, really cryptic.
content.location: to the right of guinea pig

content.description: Go up the friction slab slightly trending leftward and shoot for a nice crimp towards the top left to finish you can go straight up as well which comes in around v3
content.location: Take the trail to the left of jail house rock boulder you take to get to routes like power struggle and it will be on your right along the trail.

content.description: Stand on the ledge and get up to good rail. Slap the arete to move up and top out on some good slopers
content.location: On “The Farm” boulder. From the jailhouse rock boulder, walk down the small road like you’re heading to power struggle/zig zag and keep heading left towards the small brown cliff band. maneuver your way down the small hills to get inbetween said cliff band and small mountain to a big free standing boulder. Hard to miss.

content.description: Start with a right hand crimp and left hand sloper, on the right side of the boulder, reach your feet out to the start of the roof and keep going left along the lip until you reach the jug rail then go to the lip above.
content.location: If you go around the hill of where underbelly is you will eventually see a giant couch shaped boulder you can also see it from the dirt road off to the left

content.description: Start to the right on the obvious jug work up and left to the face through a right hand lock off to a jug sidepull, climb up to massive jug blocks to finish
content.location: Behind and to the right of casting couch boulder

content.description: start on the Gaston dish and ride the arete up
content.location: Left of pain train and rage quit

content.description: Granite climbing within an hour and a half from PHX. Mainly boulders but bolts are being drilled and plenty of granite splits ready for FA's. Most climbing is all around the big pile of boulders around the parking area in front of the “jail house” boulder
